    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. specifically for the super-fine line, we're seeing some concerns about durability if the weave is too tight. does increasing the density to create that \"impermeable barrier\" you mentioned affect the structural integrity of the linen, or does it actually make the fabric more resilient against external elements?",
